Media personality Mwanaisha Chizudga turned 38 years this week. To close her 37th chapter, Mwanaisha thanked God for having survived a road accident, contracting the deadly Covid-19 virus and her food business suffering. She said she was on the brink of giving up but thanks to her close friends and family, she found the kind of love and solace she needed. "At the same time, it has brought me a lot of joy, love, friendship lessons and hope for the future," she wrote. "Yes, Ya Allah #alhamidullilahi for all the challenges and triumph you've brought my way, and thank you for giving me the strength to overcome them." Mwanaisha added that she has learnt many lessons and survived many challenges and she still chooses to rise.